me emotions instead.Pearson makes detailed comparisons of certain Biograph films and brings a freshness to her analysis by closely examining contemporary journalistic writing, acting manuals, and the recollections of actors of the time. Her work is important for anyone interested in early cinema and performance, and it will enliven the study of American cultural history and mass communications.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMotion picture acting. 0aMovement (Acting). 0aSilent filmszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aacting manuals.  aactors.  aamerican cultural history.  aamerican director.  abiography films.  abirth of a nation.  acinema.  aclassical hollywood cinema.  acontroversy.  adw griffith.  aearly cinema.  aextreme emotion.  afeature length movie.  afilm acting.  afilm and television.  afilm theory.  ahenry d walthall.  ahollywood.  amass communication.  amovie theory.  amovies.  anarrative technique.  aperformance style.  aperforming arts.  arealistic film.  atheatrical heritage.  atrade press discourse.  aunited states of america.  averisimilar.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052007366140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520911048?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520911048423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520911048/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY